tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild hypoglycemia, elevated creatinine suggesting impaired renal function, and low HDL cholesterol, which increases cardiovascular risk. Other parameters, including liver enzymes, electrolytes, and proteins, are within normal limits. Close monitoring of renal function and glucose, as well as cardiovascular risk management, is recommended.
